*===========================================================================*
@NODE RESIDENT.PROJECT "About the Resident project.. History.."

	HISTORY

	It all started about 5 years ago, with a little unknown program
	called "InterVer" and later called "Raven". About 3 years ago I
	contacted SHI.

	This util  could be used  in the  SHI Resident project,  and it 
	should be used by the SHI antivirus team.

	For 2 years i worked on  how this util should be as powerful as
	possible. It's made to protect and analyse patches. Here is the
	answer:

	Resident.library	Version 1.417
	Resident.brainfile	Version 0.58

	---------------------------------------------------------------
	17.12.95	First  beta  version,  with a brainfile.  First 
			official SHI beta version.

			Some people had  problems  with the autodoc, it
			was placed inside a guidefile.

			Releasedata.
			------------
			Library version:	1.412 beta.
			Lib_Invalidationdate:	01.03.96
			Lib_Compilationdate:	17.12.95
			Brain version:		0.42

			Problem?
			--------
			No bugs reported. Is it really that good?   I'm
			starting to wonder..  Well it has been compiled
			some 412 times.. IT SHOULD WORK

	---------------------------------------------------------------
	04.02.96	Ahh!  finally I've  made a  util  that uses the 
			library,  it  sure  looks  good.  I added  some
			patterns to that wonderful brainfile of mine.

			It looks like the "VirusMemKill by Chris Hames,
			but its *NOT* a ripped program. Its only a test
			just to see what it looks like..

			I made  some minor changes  to the  library and 
			the brainfile. They work really fine.

			You are now  able to see how many bytes the top
			sub is using..  For no use..?  Maybe..  Well it 
			gives you an idea about how big the patch is...

			(Well that sounds stupid..=)

			Problem 1.
			----------
			Sorry! You  will not  be able to list all known
			patches in the brainfile yet.  This is a  minor
			problem  that I'm  dealing  with at the moment.

			Releasedata.
			------------
			Library version:	1.415
			Lib_Invalidationdate:	01.08.96
			Lib_Compilationdate:	04.02.96
			Brain version:		0.54

	---------------------------------------------------------------
	10.02.96	Took  my time to add some more  of  the locale-
			patches... tested my utility.. It worked..

	---------------------------------------------------------------
	23.02.96	Oh!  Time is running out!  Better get something 
			done..  Optimized  the  library and started re-
			writing the interrupts. :-<>

	---------------------------------------------------------------
	25.02.96	Ah! The Interrupts are ready phew...     I also 
			removed   the  "Unvalidation"  date   from  the 
			library... 

			Started to make the package, wrote this history
			in 2 hours.. Hmmm..

	---------------------------------------------------------------
	26.02.96	First official release.

			The  "Lib_Invalidationdate"  now  means  I will 
			release my next version before that date...

			You wont  get  this  stupid requester that says 
			"Resident.library is out of date...."

			Releasedata.
			------------
			Library version:	1.417
			Lib_Invalidationdate:	01.01.97
			Lib_Compilationdate:	26.02.96
			Brain version:		0.58
@ENDNODE
