*===========================================================================*
@NODE _LVOResOpenBrain() "_LVOResOpenBrain()"

NAME	
	_LVOResOpenBrain() -- Loads the Resident.brainfile.

SYNOPSIS
	result  = OpenBrain(APTR PATH)
	d0                  a0

FUNCTION
	Loads the brainfile, and makes it ready to be used.

INPUTS		
	PATH -- Pointer to a pathstring with name and a terminat-
	ing null. Brainfile should be found in PROGDIR: or L:

	-------->	dc.b	"L:Resident.brainfile",0

RESULT	
	NULL	=	OK, brainfile loaded. Integrity check ok.

	Errorcodes	RDM_NOTFOUND	= -1
			RDM_BRAINBAD	= -2
			RDM_BRAINLOADED	= -3 ; It allready existed.
			RDM_NOMEM	= -4
			RDM_LOADERROR	= -5

		
	IoErr() from dos will be replaced by a RDM_LOADERROR. 
	(Easy eh?)

BUGS	
	None known.

SEE ALSO
	@{" _LVOResAnalysePatch() " LINK _LVOResAnalysePatch()} @{" _LVOResScanBrainfile() " LINK _LVOResScanBrainfile()}
	@{" _LVOResGetBrainID() " LINK _LVOResGetBrainID()}          
@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE _LVOResCloseBrain() "_LVOResCloseBrain()"

NAME	
	_LVOResCloseBrain() -- UnLoads the Resident.brainfile.

SYNOPSIS
	(VOID)	= CloseBrain()

FUNCTION
	UnLoads the brainfile, and makes the library ready to be 
	closed.

INPUTS
	None.

RESULT
	None, except brainfile is gone.

BUGS
	None known.

SEE ALSO
	@{" _LVOResAnalysePatch() " LINK _LVOResAnalysePatch()} @{" _LVOResScanBrainfile() " LINK _LVOResScanBrainfile()}
	@{" _LVOResGetBrainID() " LINK _LVOResGetBrainID()}        

@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE _LVOResCreateOwner() "_LVOResCreateOwner()"
NAME
	_LVOResCreateOwner() - Creates an owner for user.

SYNOPSIS
	result	=	_LVOResCreateOwner()
	d0

FUNCTION
	Creates an owner for 'Resident.library', without this structure you
	wont be able to do anything in the future, this structure knows al-
	most everything	about your process or task.

	Structure is inserted to an internal and 'secret' list.   This list 
	is unaccessable for coders,  this means *ONLY* Resident.library can 
	access it.  It's  holding  information about  your process  that is 
	vital for any use of the library.

	When installed, a port will appear in portlist with the library ID.

	Task pointer to name will be checked,  taskbase,  hmm..  do we need 
	anything else? This function will guard your process in the future,
	YES! that is true! Guard your process. This means anyone who decide
	to remove you without your permission, will fail!

CAUTION
	Dont change your process name while using owner structure.

	This function can only be called from process. Else it wont work or
	even crach your amiga. Well, so far it needs the Kick 2.04  or V36.

	You *can* open a brainfile and scan patches without this structure.

INPUT
	None.

RESULT
	Boolean.

	True (1) 	= Owner created and inserted to list.
	False (0)	= Structure was not created and nor inserted to the
			  list.

FAILURES
	maybe the "Owner" already existed?? You only need to create once.
	If not successfull, try to free mem!

BUGS
	None known.

SEE ALSO
        @{" _LVOResDeleteOwner() " LINK _LVOResDeleteOwner()}
@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE _LVOResDeleteOwner() "_LVOResDeleteOwner()"
NAME
	_LVOResDeleteOwner() - Deletes an owner structure.

SYNOPSIS
	result	=	_LVOResDeleteOwner()
	d0

FUNCTION
	Removes and deallocates your owner structure,  any contents will be
	removed also.

INPUT
	None.

RESULT
	True (1) 	= Successfully removed.
	False (0)	= Already removed? You didn't own a structure?!?
			  Well, only free once.. :-)

BUGS
	None known.

SEE ALSO
        @{" _LVOResCreateOwner() " LINK _LVOResCreateOwner()}
@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE _LVOResAnalysePatch() "_LVOResAnalysePatch()"

NAME
	_LVOResAnalysePatch() -- Get the integrity of a patch.

SYNOPSIS
	result  = AnalysePatch(APTR PATCH, APTR PATCH_SIZE)
	d0                     a0          a1

FUNCTION
	When a positive analyse is done, it fills out Name, ID, 
	Function, Author and subsize...

	Subsize is the upper part of the sub.. so far.

INPUTS
	PATCH		-- Pointer to a patch.
	PATCH_SIZE	-- Pointer to a structure that should be filled
			   out with the patch information.

			(PATCH_STRUCTURE is found in "resident.i").

			Make sure to use the complete PATCH_SIZE,
			and innocent data wont be overrun.

		     STRUCTURE	PATCHNODE,0
		       STRUCT	PATCH_NEXTNODE,4
			APTR	PATCH_NAME
			APTR	PATCH_ID
			APTR	PATCH_FUNCTION
			APTR	PATCH_AUTHOR
			LONG	PATCH_SUBSIZE

			;! OBSOLETE AND PRIVATE !

			UBYTE	PATCH_PAASTATE
			UBYTE	PATCH_PABSTATE

			ULONG	PATCH_BASE
			ULONG	PATCH_OFFSETBASE
			ULONG	PATCH_OFFSET
			UWORD	PATCH_MACHINE
			UWORD	PATCH_VALID
			ULONG	PATCH_BASENAME
			ULONG	PATCH_FUNCNAME
			ULONG	PATCH_CODE
			ULONG	PATCH_PATTERN_POS_B
			ULONG	PATCH_PATTERN_INS_B
			ULONG	PATCH_PATTERN_POS_W
			ULONG	PATCH_PATTERN_INS_W
			ULONG	PATCH_PATTERN_POS_L
			ULONG	PATCH_PATTERN_INS_L
			ULONG	PATCH_CHECKSUM
			LABEL	PATCH_SIZE


CHANGES
	PATCH_ID is now containig the vector name. Ex. RawDoFmt found in
	exec...

@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE _LVOResScanBrainfile() "_LVOResScanBrainfile()"

NAME
	_LVOResScanBrainfile() -- Analyze the loaded brainfile.

SYNOPSIS
	result	= _LVOResScanBrainfile()
	d0

FUNCTION
	This function is called when using the _LVOResOpenBrainfile(), it
	simply checks out the integrity of the brainfile.

INPUTS
	None

RESULT
	NULL	= OK, brain is fine.
	1	= Failure, please remove it.

BUGS
	None known.
@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE _LVOResGetBrainID() "_LVOResGetBrainID()"

NAME
	_LVOResGetBrainID() -- Gets ID string from Resident.Brainfile.

SYNOPSIS
	result	= _LVOResGetBrainID()
	d0

FUNCTION
	Gets ID string from brainfile, if brainfile is loaded.

INPUTS
	None.

RESULT
	NULL	= ERROR.
	PTR	= STRING.

BUGS
	None known.
@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE _LVOResReset() "_LVOResReset()"

NAME
	_LVOResReset() -- Kills system.

SYNOPSIS
	_LVOResReset()

FUNCTION
	Makes an ultimate reset with a little help from the system, and if
	system is patched by something, it will cheat system and reset any
	way. Patch won't be used.

INPUTS
	None.

RESULT
	Coldreset.

BUGS
	I want this to work on all systems, so please notify me if you get
	any problems with it.

	In future versions execbase will  be totaly  eliminated before any
	reset.
@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE LIBRARY "What is a library?"

  A  library is a system util containing functions that all programs have
  access to. The program needs to open the library before usage.

  After the usage your program should close the library again so that the
  system memory may be free again.

  Libraryfiles can be found in "LIBS:"

@ENDNODE
*===========================================================================*
@NODE BRAINFILE "What is a brainfile?"

  A  Brainfile is a kind of a loadable part for holding information about
  sertain definition codes. This could be machinecode or just saved data.

  Resident.brainfile should always be in the L: directory.  But you could 
  put it in any other directory if your virus killer uses that.

  L: is the standard, so use it.

@ENDNODE



